.18.2.9536488">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/9536488/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Mucinous+cystic+neoplasms+of+the+pancreas%3A+radiologic-pathologic+correlation&amp;author=PC+Buetow&amp;author=P+Rao&amp;author=LD+Thompson&amp;publication_year=1998&amp;journal=RadioGraphics&amp;pages=433-449&amp;doi=10.1148%2Fradiographics.18.2.9536488&amp;pmid=9536488">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">60.</div><div id="r60" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Zen Y, Jang KT, Ahn S, et al. Intraductal papillary neoplasms and mucinous cystic neoplasms of the hepatobiliary system: demographic differences between Asian and Western populations, and comparison with pancreatic counterparts. <em>Histopathology</em> 2014;65(2):164–173.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1111/his.12378">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/24456415/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Intraductal+papillary+neoplasms+and+mucinous+cystic+neoplasms+of+the+hepatobiliary+system%3A+demographic+differences+between+Asian+and+Western+populations%2C+and+comparison+with+pancreatic+counterparts&amp;author=Y+Zen&amp;author=KT+Jang&amp;author=S+Ahn&amp;publication_year=2014&amp;journal=Histopathology&amp;pages=164-173&amp;doi=10.1111%2Fhis.12378&amp;pmid=24456415">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">61.</div><div id="r61" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Matsubara T, Sato Y, Sasaki M, et al. Immunohistochemical characteristics and malignant progression of hepatic cystic neoplasms in comp